Popular Afrikaans singer Robbie Wessel's paid tribute Springboks captain Siya Kolisi with a beautiful song. JOHANNESBURG - Afrikaans singer Robbie Wessels paid tribute to Springboks captain Siya Kolisi with a special song. WATCH: Kolisi vows to make a change Earlier this month, Kolisi made history by becoming the first black captain to lead the team to a World Cup victory in Japan. The upbeat song encourages unity and reaching out to help others when they are in trouble, regardless of their race or culture.